  { id:197, subject:"AFM", standard:"Mutual Funds", category:"Quick Fire", difficulty:"Intermediate",
    front:"вљЎ MATCH: Which ratio uses which risk measure?\n\nA. Sharpe Ratio\nB. Treynor Ratio\nC. Sortino Ratio\nD. Jensen's Alpha",
    back:"A. Sharpe в†’ Standard Deviation (Total Risk)\n\nB. Treynor в†’ Beta (Systematic Risk only)\n\nC. Sortino в†’ Downside Deviation only (not full SD)\n\nD. Jensen's Alpha в†’ Beta via CAPM\n   (Actual Return в€’ CAPM Expected Return)\n\nв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nрџ“Њ Memory trick:\nвЂў SHARP в†’ Standard deviation\nвЂў TREYNOR в†’ TRacks Beta\nвЂў SorTINO в†’ only downside TIN (negative)\nвЂў Jensen = Excess alpha above CAPM",
    exam:false },

  // Minor improvement: added "NAV drops ex-dividend" note
  { id:198, subject:"AFM", standard:"Mutual Funds", category:"Quick Fire", difficulty:"Intermediate",
    front:"вљЎ What happens to NAV when a dividend is declared and paid out?",
    back:"рџ“‰ NAV FALLS by the amount of dividend paid out (on ex-dividend date).\n\nExample:\nNAV before dividend = в‚№16\nDividend paid = в‚№4 per unit\nNAV after dividend = в‚№12 (ex-dividend NAV)\n\nв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nOptions for investors:\n\n1. Dividend Payout: Receive cash; NAV falls\n2. Dividend Reinvestment: Cash reinvested at ex-dividend NAV; get more units; NAV still falls but unit count increases\n3. Growth Option: No dividend; NAV keeps growing until you sell\n\nрџ“Њ In dividend reinvestment, total investment value remains same on ex-dividend date вЂ” only unit count changes.",
    exam:false },
  { id:199, subject:"AFM", standard:"Mutual Funds", category:"Quick Fire", difficulty:"Advanced",
    front:"вљЎ Which fund type is close-ended by SEBI mandate?\n\nA. ETF\nB. Capital Protection Oriented Fund\nC. Real Estate MF (REMF)\nD. Both B and C",
    back:"вњ… Answer: D вЂ” Both B and C\n\nрџ“‹ Capital Protection Oriented Fund:\nв†’ Must be CLOSE-ENDED\nв†’ Listed on stock exchange\nв†’ Portfolio structure rated by credit rating agency\nв†’ Invests majority in high-rated debt + some equity for appreciation\nв†’ в‰  Capital Guaranteed (no bank guarantee)\n\nрџЏ  Real Estate MF (REMF):\nв†’ Close-ended by nature\nв†’ Listed on stock exchange\nв†’ Earns rentals + capital appreciation\nв†’ Also invests in equity/debentures of real estate companies",
    exam:false },
  { id:200, subject:"AFM", standard:"Mutual Funds", category:"Quick Fire", difficulty:"Basic",
    front:"вљЎ What does ELSS stand for and what are its key features?",
    back:"ELSS = Equity Linked Savings Scheme\n\nKey Features:\nвњ… Tax saving under Section 80C of Income Tax Act\nвњ… Lock-in period: 3 YEARS (shortest among all 80C instruments)\nвњ… Invests in equity в†’ potential for higher returns vs traditional tax savers\nвњ… Can invest via SIP (benefit of rupee cost averaging)\n\nрџ“Њ Comparison with other 80C instruments:\nвЂў PPF: 15 years lock-in\nвЂў ELSS: 3 years lock-in в†’ most liquid tax-saving option\nвЂў NSC: 5 years\n\nрџ“Њ ELSS = equity-oriented; hence higher risk but higher potential returns.",
    exam:false },
  { id:201, subject:"AFM", standard:"Mutual Funds", category:"Quick Fire", difficulty:"Intermediate",
    front:"вљЎ What is a Fund of Funds (FoF)?",
    back:"рџ“¦ Fund of Funds = Mutual fund scheme that invests in OTHER mutual fund schemes (not directly in securities)\n\nKey Points:\nвЂў Underlying investment = units of other MF schemes\nвЂў From same fund family OR other fund houses\nвЂў Popular where MF offerings are numerous and choosing is complex\n\nExample: Indian MFs investing in International MF schemes\n\nPros:\nвњ… Diversification across fund managers\nвњ… Access to international markets easily\n\nCons:\nвќЊ Double expense ratio (own + underlying fund's expense)\n\nрџ“Њ FoF is categorized under Special Funds in Portfolio Classification.",
    exam:false },
  { id:202, subject:"AFM", standard:"Mutual Funds", category:"Quick Fire", difficulty:"Basic",
    front:"вљЎ Full form & meaning:\nAMFI | AMC | NFO | SIP | SWP | TER",
    back:"рџ“‹ Quick Reference:\n\nAMFI в†’ Association of Mutual Funds in India\n(Publishes daily NAV, regulates distributors)\n\nAMC в†’ Asset Management Company\n(Manages the MF; runs schemes; TER capped per SEBI AUM slabs)\n\nNFO в†’ New Fund Offer\n(Like IPO for MFs; initial subscription period)\n\nSIP в†’ Systematic Investment Plan\n(Regular fixed investment at intervals)\n\nSWP в†’ Systematic Withdrawal Plan\n(Regular fixed withdrawal from investment)\n\nTER в†’ Total Expense Ratio\n(Same as MER вЂ” Management Expense Ratio)\n\nрџ“Њ NAV published daily through AMFI in newspapers.",
    exam:false }